The HD 155233 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 155233 is a star with 1.69 times the mass of the Sun, and 5.03 times its radius. It is located 242.11 light years away from the solar system.

HD 155233 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 155233 system


HD 155233 b

HD 155233 b was discovered by the Anglo-Australian Telescope observatory, in 2016-01, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 2.00 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 155233 b is 826.800 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 155233 b is 13.200 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 155233 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
